Description: Fragment of neck and shoulder, with trace of handle root, of East Greek pottery closed vase, probably an amphora; cream slip on exterior; interior reserved; exterior: neck reserved; glaze line on slight moulding at turn to shoulder; shoulder zone reserved with band of degenerate florals alternating with concentric circles with large central disc.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1165)
